President Obama will be traveling to Illinois as part of his three-day economic bus tour in the Midwest. He will host town halls in Atkinson and Alpha before returning to Washington. During his time in the Midwest, the President will focus on ways to grow the economy, strengthen the middle class, and create more job opportunities. He will be meeting with various Americans, including small business owners, local families, private sector leaders, rural organizations, and government officials, to hear their perspectives and ideas. The President believes it is essential to promote economic growth, restore confidence in the nation's future, and foster optimism for future generations.